---
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';

const categories = [
  {
    label: 'Writing',
    prompts: [
      {
        title: 'Email reply that sounds like you',
        body: `You are an editor who writes in a clear, warm, no-fluff voice — short sentences, contractions OK, no corporate hedging. Below is an email I received and a rough draft of my reply. Rewrite my reply in that voice. Keep my actual points; tighten the wording, cut throat-clearing, and end with a clear next step. Return only the rewritten email.

EMAIL I RECEIVED:
[paste]

MY DRAFT REPLY:
[paste]`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Tighten this paragraph',
        body: `You are a ruthless line editor. Cut filler, replace weak verbs, remove throat-clearing, and shorten wherever possible without losing meaning. Keep the original tone. Return: (1) the tightened version, (2) a short bullet list of what you cut and why.

PARAGRAPH:
[paste]`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Translate into plain language',
        body: `Rewrite the text below for a smart but non-expert reader. No jargon — if a technical term is essential, define it inline. Aim for short sentences and concrete examples. Preserve every fact; do not add new claims. Return only the rewritten version.

TEXT:
[paste]`,
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    label: 'Meetings',
    prompts: [
      {
        title: 'Pre-meeting brief',
        body: `You are my chief of staff. I have a meeting with [name/role] in [time] about [topic]. Based on the notes below (and any recent context you have), give me:
1. A one-line goal for the meeting
2. The 3 questions I should ask
3. The 2 most likely points of pushback and how I'd handle each
4. One thing I should NOT bring up

NOTES / CONTEXT:
[paste]`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Summarize meeting notes into actions',
        body: `Read the meeting notes below. Produce two outputs:
1. A 5-bullet executive summary
2. An action list with columns: owner, action, due date (use "TBD" if not mentioned)

Don't invent owners or deadlines. If the notes are ambiguous, flag it instead of guessing.

NOTES:
[paste]`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Draft a follow-up email',
        body: `Below are my notes from a meeting with [name]. Draft a follow-up email from me to them that: thanks them, summarizes what was decided in 3 short bullets, names the next concrete step with an owner and date, and ends with a clear question. Match my voice — direct, friendly, no jargon. Keep it under 150 words.

NOTES:
[paste]`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Pull decisions and action items from a transcript',
        body: `Below is a meeting transcript. Read the whole thing, then return two clean tables.

DECISIONS — every decision the group actually agreed on. Columns: decision, who decided, why (if stated). Skip ideas that were floated but not resolved.

ACTION ITEMS — every concrete to-do. Columns: owner, action, due date (use "TBD" if not stated), source quote (the exact line that established it).

Rules: don't invent owners, deadlines, or decisions. If a line is ambiguous about ownership or commitment, list it under a third "NEEDS CLARIFICATION" section instead of guessing. End with a one-sentence note flagging anything important that was discussed but left unresolved.

TRANSCRIPT:
[paste]`,
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    label: 'Strategy & analysis',
    prompts: [
      {
        title: 'Steelman the other side',
        body: `I'm leaning toward [decision/position]. Steelman the strongest case AGAINST it — not strawman objections, the most rigorous version a smart critic would actually make. Give me 4–6 points, each with a one-sentence rebuttal I'd need to have ready. End with: "If you only address one of these, address [X]" and explain why.

CONTEXT:
[paste]`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Pre-mortem on a decision',
        body: `It's six months from now and the decision below failed. Walk me through the most likely failure mode: what specifically went wrong, what early signals would have warned us, and what we should change about the plan now to avoid it. Be concrete; no generic risk-register filler.

DECISION:
[paste]`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Compare options on the criteria that matter',
        body: `I'm choosing between [option A], [option B], and [option C] for [purpose]. The criteria I actually care about are [list]. Build a comparison table: rows = criteria, columns = options. In each cell, give a short verdict (1–2 sentences) — not a score. End with a one-paragraph recommendation that names tradeoffs explicitly.

CONTEXT:
[paste]`,
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    label: 'Documents',
    prompts: [
      {
        title: 'Contract risk scan',
        body: `You are a careful contract reviewer (not a lawyer). Read the contract attached. Output:
1. A 5-bullet plain-language summary of what we're agreeing to
2. The 3 clauses most likely to bite us, with the exact quoted text and why it matters
3. Anything that looks unusual compared to a standard [agreement type]
4. A list of questions to ask before signing

I am the [your role/company]. Counterparty is [their role/company].`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Compare two documents',
        body: `Compare the two documents attached. Produce: (1) a one-paragraph summary of the key differences, (2) a side-by-side table of every meaningful change, (3) a flag list of any change a reasonable reader might miss. Quote exact text in the comparison cells.`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Summarize a long PDF for an exec',
        body: `Summarize the attached document for a busy executive who has 60 seconds. Format:
- One-sentence TL;DR
- 3 bullets of the most important findings
- 2 bullets on what the exec needs to decide or do
- One quote (with page number) that captures the document's heart

No fluff. No "in conclusion." Cut anything that doesn't pay rent.`,
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    label: 'Slides & presentations',
    prompts: [
      {
        title: 'Outline a deck from a brief',
        body: `Outline a [length]-minute presentation for [audience] on [topic]. Output a slide-by-slide list with a title, a one-sentence purpose, and 3–5 bullet points of content per slide. Keep cognitive load light — each slide should make one point. Open strong (a question or surprise), not with an agenda slide.

BRIEF:
[paste]`,
      },
      {
        title: 'Tighten my slide titles',
        body: `Below are slide titles from my deck. Rewrite each as a short, declarative sentence that states the slide's single takeaway — not its topic. ("Q3 Revenue" → "Q3 revenue grew 22%, driven by enterprise.") Keep my voice; cut hedges. Return as a numbered list matching my input order.

TITLES:
[paste]`,
      },
    ],
  },
];
---
<Section id="prompt-library" number="06" title="Prompt Library" band="dark">
  <p>
    Copy-paste prompts you can use today. Each one starts with role and task, gives the model the context
    it needs, and tells it the format you want back — the RTCF framework in action. Replace the
    <code>[bracketed bits]</code> with your own details.
  </p>

  <div class="prompt-grid">
    {categories.map((cat) => (
      <div class="prompt-cat">
        <h4 class="prompt-cat-title">{cat.label}</h4>
        <div class="prompt-cards">
          {cat.prompts.map((p) => (
            <article class="prompt-card">
              <header class="prompt-card-head">
                <h5>{p.title}</h5>
                <button class="copy-btn" type="button" data-copy data-label="Copy" data-success="Copied!">
                  <span class="copy-btn-text">Copy</span>
                </button>
              </header>
              <pre class="prompt-card-body"><code>{p.body}</code></pre>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</Section>

<script>
  const buttons = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('button[data-copy]');
  buttons.forEach((btn) => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
      const card = btn.closest('article.prompt-card');
      const code = card?.querySelector('code')?.textContent ?? '';
      try {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(code);
        const text = btn.querySelector('.copy-btn-text');
        if (text) text.textContent = btn.dataset.success ?? 'Copied!';
        btn.classList.add('copy-btn--success');
        window.setTimeout(() => {
          if (text) text.textContent = btn.dataset.label ?? 'Copy';
          btn.classList.remove('copy-btn--success');
        }, 1600);
      } catch (e) {
        const text = btn.querySelector('.copy-btn-text');
        if (text) text.textContent = 'Press Cmd+C';
      }
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .prompt-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 48px;
    margin: 40px 0 0 0;
  }
  .prompt-cat-title {
    font-size: 14px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--brand-blue);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 18px 0;
  }
  .prompt-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(360px, 1fr));
    gap: 18px;
  }
  .prompt-card {
    background: #ffffff;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 102, 204, 0.25);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--brand-blue);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 31, 63, 0.18);
  }
  .prompt-card-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 102, 204, 0.18);
    background: rgba(0, 102, 204, 0.05);
  }
  .prompt-card-head h5 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--dark-gray);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .copy-btn {
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 102, 204, 0.5);
    background: white;
    color: var(--brand-blue);
    padding: 6px 12px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease, color 0.15s ease;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .copy-btn:hover {
    background: var(--brand-blue);
    border-color: var(--brand-blue);
    color: white;
  }
  .copy-btn--success {
    background: rgba(0, 153, 76, 0.12);
    border-color: rgba(0, 153, 76, 0.6);
    color: #008142;
  }
  .copy-btn--success:hover {
    background: rgba(0, 153, 76, 0.12);
    color: #008142;
  }
  .prompt-card-body {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 16px 18px;
    background: #ffffff;
    color: var(--dark-gray);
    font-family: 'SF Mono', Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    word-wrap: break-word;
    flex: 1;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
  .prompt-card-body code {
    background: transparent;
    color: inherit;
    padding: 0;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: inherit;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .prompt-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
